$ Powershell module: filesystem

{ Functions

  table { ll
    `initialize-emptyDirectory $dir` ☰ Creates an *empty directory* named `$dir` and returns the corresponding → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/DirectoryInfo[`System.IO.DirectoryInfo`] object.. If `$dir` already exists, it is removed (including content). If the directory cannot be removed, the function returns → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/null[`$null`]
    → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/filesystem/resolve-relativePath[`resolve-relativePath`] ☰ Returns the *relative path* between a directory and a (single or → Windows/PowerShell/language/type/array of) file(s) or directory(s). (Inspired by → https://github.com/webmd-health-services/Carbon/[Carbon's] command → https://get-carbon.org/Resolve-RelativePath.html[`Resolve-RelativePath`], uses the → Windows/development/WinAPI function `PathRelativePathTo`).
    → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/filesystem/write-file[`write-file`] ☰ Creates or overwrites a file whose content is given in a string. Necessary paths of the destination directory are created.
  table }

}

